Abia State Police Command has announced the rescue of a Chinese national abducted in the state by a team of security agents. The commandâ€™s Public Relations Officer, ASP Maureen Chinaka who confirmed the release on Wednesday said that the Chinese national, Mr Li Peiyin, abducted on May 31, was rescued by a joint security team in good condition on Monday. Peiyin, who was the site Manager of a quarry in Lokpanta, Umunneochi Local Government Area, was driving in a Caterpillar without a security escort when he was abducted. Chinaka said that the joint security team had sustained a manhunt for the abductors.